{"article_id":"8nzcRjmnl6bVlOTE","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The United States will maintain the threat of military force against Syria with efforts underway","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"to diplomatically place its chemical weapons under international control ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"President Barack Obama said on Saturday .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"His comments came","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"as Secretary of State John Kerry and his Russian counterpart , Sergey Lavrov , continued their initial round of talks in Geneva on ways","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"to forge a peaceful resolution with international backing .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"While senior administration officials said on Friday","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the United States would not insist","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that the threat of military force be included in a potential U.N. resolution on Syria ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Obama said in his weekly address","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that it was important for it to exist outside of that diplomatic process ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"which could last for weeks at least .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"`` Since this plan emerged only with a credible threat of U.S. military action ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"we will maintain our military posture in the region","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"to keep the pressure on the Assad regime , ''","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"`` And","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"if diplomacy fails ,","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"the United States and the international community must remain prepared to act . ''","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"A senior defense official told CNN","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"there has been `` no change '' in the military 's planning or readiness levels","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and commanders have not been instructed to change their `` posture '' in any way .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Russia ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"which can block action in the U.N. Security Council ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"opposes the threat of force in any resolution .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Obama said","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"the surprise diplomatic opening","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that materialized earlier this week","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"can not be a stall tactic .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"`` Any agreement needs to verify","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"that the Assad regime and Russia are keeping their commitments :","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that means working to turn Syria 's chemical weapons over to international control","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"and ultimately destroying them , ''","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"`` we need to see concrete actions","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"to demonstrate","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"that Assad is serious about giving up his chemical weapons . ''","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"The Obama administration contends","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"the Syrian regime","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"led by President Bashar al-Assad","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"launched a poison gas attack on civilians outside Damascus on August 21 ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"killing more than 1,400 people .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Obama sought authorization from Congress for a limited military strike","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"to punish the Syrian regime ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"which has denied being behind the chemical attack .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"He paused that effort amid weak support from lawmakers in both houses","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"to give diplomacy a chance .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"This week ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"when I addressed the nation on Syria ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"I said","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"- in part because of the credible threat of U.S. military force -","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"there is the possibility of a diplomatic solution .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Russia has indicated a new willingness","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"to join with the international community","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"in pushing Syria to give up its chemical weapons ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"which the Assad regime used in an attack","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"that killed more than 1,000 people on August 21 .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"I also asked Congress to postpone a vote on the use of military force","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"while we pursue this diplomatic path .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"And that 's what we 're doing .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"At my direction , Secretary of State Kerry is in discussions with his Russian counterpart .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"But we 're making it clear","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"that this ca n't be a stalling tactic .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Any agreement needs to verify","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that the Assad regime and Russia are keeping their commitments :","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"that means working to turn Syria 's chemical weapons over to international control","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"and ultimately destroying them .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"This would allow us to achieve our goal","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"- deterring the Syrian regime from using chemical weapons ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"degrading their ability","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"to use them ,","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"and making it clear to the world","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"that we wo n't tolerate their use .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"We 've seen indications of progress .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"As recently as a week ago , the Assad regime would not admit","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that it possessed chemical weapons .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Today , it does .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Syria has signaled a willingness to join with 189 other nations ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"representing 98 percent of humanity ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"in abiding by an international agreement","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"that prohibits the use of chemical weapons .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"And Russia has staked its own credibility","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"on supporting this outcome .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"These are all positive developments .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"We 'll keep working with the international community","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"to see","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"that Assad gives up his chemical weapons","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"so that they can be destroyed .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"We will continue rallying support from allies around the world","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"who agree on the need for action","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"to deter the use of chemical weapons in Syria .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"if current discussions produce a serious plan ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"I 'm prepared to move forward with it .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"But we are not just going to take Russia and Assad 's word for it .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"We need to see concrete actions","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"to demonstrate","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"that Assad is serious about giving up his chemical weapons .","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"since this plan emerged only with a credible threat of U.S. military action ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"we will maintain our military posture in the region","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"to keep the pressure on the Assad regime .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"if diplomacy fails ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"the United States and the international community must remain prepared to act .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"The use of chemical weapons anywhere in the world is an affront to human dignity and a threat to the security of people everywhere .","depth":4},{"id":109,"text":"As I have said for weeks ,","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"the international community must respond to this outrage .","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"A dictator must not be allowed to gas children in their beds with impunity .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"And we can not risk poison gas becoming the new weapon of choice for tyrants and terrorists the world over .","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"We have a duty","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"to preserve a world free from the fear of chemical weapons for our children .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"if there is any chance","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"of achieving that goal","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"without resorting to force ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"then I believe","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"we have a responsibility to pursue that path .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"Thank you .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":243,"left":0,"right":242,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":242,"left":228,"right":241,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":169,"right":227,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":146,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":127,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":124,"right":126,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":4,"right":125,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":132,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":129,"right":131,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":129,"left":7,"right":128,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":128,"lef